Venice Admin Tool
-----------------

For directly affecting administrative actions and queries on a Venice cluster

```
usage: java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --<command> [parameters]
            Commands:
    --add-schema           Requires: --router, --cluster, --store,
                           --value-schema-file
    --available-versions   Requires: --router, --cluster, --store
    --current-version      Requires: --router, --cluster, --store
    --describe-store       Requires: --router, --cluster, --store
    --describe-stores      Requires: --router, --cluster
    --job-status           Requires: --router, --cluster, --store,
                           --version
    --list-replicas        Requires: --router, --cluster, --store,
                           --version
    --list-storage-nodes   Requires: --router, --cluster
    --list-stores          Requires: --router, --cluster
    --new-store            Requires: --router, --cluster, --store,
                           --version, --key-schema-file,
                           --value-schema-file
    --next-version         Requires: --router, --cluster, --store
    --set-version          Requires: --router, --cluster, --store,
                           --version
usage: Parameters:
 -c,--cluster <arg>              Name of Venice cluster
 -h,--help                       Show usage
 -ks,--key-schema-file <arg>     Path to text file with key schema
 -o,--owner <arg>                Owner email for new store creation
 -r,--router <arg>               Venice router url, eg.
                                 http://localhost:54333
 -s,--store <arg>                Name of Venice store
 -v,--version <arg>              Venice store version number
 -vs,--value-schema-file <arg>   Path to text file with value schema

Examples:
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --list-stores --router <router> --cluster <cluster>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --describe-store --router <router> --cluster <cluster> --store <store>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --describe-stores --router <router> --cluster <cluster>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --next-version --router <router> --cluster <cluster> --store <store>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --current-version --router <router> --cluster <cluster> --store <store>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --available-versions --router <router> --cluster <cluster> --store <store>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --job-status --router <router> --cluster <cluster> --store <store> --version <version>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --new-store --router <router> --cluster <cluster> --store <store> --version <version> --key-schema-file <key-schema-file> --value-schema-file <value-schema-file>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --set-version --router <router> --cluster <cluster> --store <store> --version <version>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --add-schema --router <router> --cluster <cluster> --store <store> --value-schema-file <value-schema-file>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --list-storage-nodes --router <router> --cluster <cluster>
java -jar venice-admin-tool-0.1.jar --list-replicas --router <router> --cluster <cluster> --store <store> --version <version>
```

## Overview of Queries

Note:  All queries require a router (of form `http://<host>:<port>`) and a cluster.

### NEXT

Requires: store

Next available (unreserved) version number.  Returns an integer.

### AVAILABLE

Requires: store

All version numbers that the storage nodes can serve.  These are the only versions that we can set as current (for example for a rollback).  Returns a list of integers, eg: [3, 4]

### CURRENT

Requires: store

The version that is currently being served by the router.  Returns an integer.

### JOB

Requires: store, version

Job status for storage node consumption.

### LIST

Displays (newline delimited) all stores in the cluster

### DESCRIBE

Displays all version information about all stores in the cluster.  If a store is specified, then it only shows details for that store.

```
Store: myCountry2	Available versions: [1]	Current version: 1	Next version: 2
Store: myCountry	Available versions: [2, 3, 4]	Current version: 4	Next version: 6
```

## Overview of New

### STORE

Requires: store, owner, key-schema-file, value-schema-file

Creates a new store.

## Overview of Apply

### VERSION

Requires: store, version

Sets the specified version to active for the specified store

### SCHEMA

Requires: store, value-schema-file

Adds the specified value schema to the store

